1
00:01:35,240 --> 00:01:39,960
[This Thriving Land]

2
00:01:40,360 --> 00:01:42,910
[Episode 10]

3
00:01:44,310 --> 00:01:45,870
It's not really a discussion, to be fair.

4
00:01:45,870 --> 00:01:47,400
I want to beg you for a favor.

5
00:01:47,460 --> 00:01:48,920
No need to beg—just say it.

6
00:01:56,310 --> 00:01:57,560
Pacing, pacing...

7
00:01:57,560 --> 00:01:59,430
You're making me dizzy. Stop it!

8
00:02:00,710 --> 00:02:02,870
It's been quite a while now.

9
00:02:04,890 --> 00:02:06,700
Dajiao, go eavesdrop—

10
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:09,030
see if they mention the land.

11
00:02:09,520 --> 00:02:10,520
No, I'm not going.

12
00:02:10,750 --> 00:02:12,280
They're sisters chatting—

13
00:02:12,360 --> 00:02:13,910
what am I supposed to do there?

14
00:02:13,910 --> 00:02:15,310
Is Miss Susu not leaving?

15
00:02:15,840 --> 00:02:16,900
No, she's staying.

16
00:02:17,240 --> 00:02:18,640
Let them have a good chat.

17
00:02:18,800 --> 00:02:19,260
Mother.

18
00:02:19,470 --> 00:02:21,030
Let me sleep here tonight.

19
00:02:21,870 --> 00:02:22,930
Yes, that's right.

20
00:02:23,120 --> 00:02:24,190
Let them chat—

21
00:02:24,770 --> 00:02:26,430
they'll get to the land soon enough.

22
00:02:26,430 --> 00:02:28,470
What's so hard about this?

23
00:02:28,470 --> 00:02:30,240
You should've said so earlier.

24
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:32,710
Perhaps Feng Er and Feng Dajiao
already have land!

25
00:02:32,710 --> 00:02:34,170
It's not that simple.

26
00:02:34,310 --> 00:02:35,710
I don't want Mrs. Fei

27
00:02:35,710 --> 00:02:37,030
to think I'd only rent your land

28
00:02:37,030 --> 00:02:38,190
because I'm desperate.

29
00:02:38,190 --> 00:02:39,120
Xiuxiu, listen—

30
00:02:39,470 --> 00:02:40,240
this is just land rental,

31
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:41,590
you're not taking it from her!

32
00:02:41,590 --> 00:02:43,250
You'll still pay rent, right?

33
00:02:43,430 --> 00:02:45,150
I always hear Mrs. Fei

34
00:02:45,150 --> 00:02:46,520
telling that Beard Liu:

35
00:02:46,520 --> 00:02:48,240
"lease the land to someone,

36
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:49,870
go write up a rental contract,

37
00:02:49,870 --> 00:02:51,590
and it's done!" Simple as that.

38
00:02:51,590 --> 00:02:53,590
What's the difference who rents it?

39
00:02:54,750 --> 00:02:57,030
No wonder Mother
used to say you were sharp!

40
00:02:57,030 --> 00:02:58,590
You really are—

41
00:02:59,180 --> 00:02:59,970
it's such a big deal,

42
00:02:59,970 --> 00:03:02,700
and you made it crystal clear
in three sentences!

43
00:03:02,710 --> 00:03:04,630
Will you help me
communicate with Mrs. Fei?

44
00:03:04,630 --> 00:03:06,360
Don't you worry—I've got this!

45
00:03:08,870 --> 00:03:09,680
Is it cold?

46
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:10,740
Your bed is so warm!

47
00:03:11,030 --> 00:03:11,910
As soon as I sit down here,

48
00:03:11,910 --> 00:03:13,000
I feel warm all over.

49
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:14,400
I really don't want to leave now.

50
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:15,240
Don't go, then.

51
00:03:15,240 --> 00:03:16,900
Stay here for a couple nights.

52
00:03:18,780 --> 00:03:19,250
Xiu...

53
00:03:20,450 --> 00:03:22,610
Mrs. Fei's here to take Susu home.

54
00:03:23,560 --> 00:03:25,020
-Xiuxiu.
-Why is she here?

55
00:03:26,250 --> 00:03:28,250
Susu's been out all day,

56
00:03:28,280 --> 00:03:29,280
and she still isn't back yet.

57
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:30,880
I got worried, so I came over.

58
00:03:31,690 --> 00:03:33,740
Susu. Let's go home.

59
00:03:34,510 --> 00:03:37,070
I was thinking of staying
at Xiu's place tonight.

60
00:03:37,070 --> 00:03:38,070
Mrs. Fei.

61
00:03:38,710 --> 00:03:40,710
Will you let Susu stay for the night?

62
00:03:41,510 --> 00:03:42,320
Susu,

63
00:03:42,870 --> 00:03:44,530
let's not be so willful, okay?

64
00:03:44,600 --> 00:03:46,350
Look how late it is.

65
00:03:46,370 --> 00:03:47,310
You're still here, bothering

66
00:03:47,310 --> 00:03:48,579
your sister and her husband!

67
00:03:48,579 --> 00:03:49,440
If you wanna chat,

68
00:03:49,440 --> 00:03:51,240
there'll be plenty of time later.

69
00:03:51,240 --> 00:03:52,900
You may come back another day.

70
00:03:52,950 --> 00:03:53,329
Come on here.

71
00:03:53,329 --> 00:03:54,970
I even brought your coat.

72
00:03:58,150 --> 00:03:59,190
Mrs. Fei.

73
00:03:59,770 --> 00:04:00,800
It's our

74
00:04:00,830 --> 00:04:02,520
first New Year apart.

75
00:04:02,540 --> 00:04:04,190
We just want to talk the night through—

76
00:04:04,190 --> 00:04:06,100
I'll have her home by sunrise.

77
00:04:06,180 --> 00:04:07,460
Please, Mrs. Fei...

78
00:04:07,570 --> 00:04:09,080
at my sister's place—

79
00:04:09,100 --> 00:04:10,110
just one night. That's all.

80
00:04:10,110 --> 00:04:13,050
After all this time,
you still won't address me properly?

81
00:04:13,050 --> 00:04:14,770
Who's really family here?

82
00:04:19,110 --> 00:04:19,910
Get down here.

83
00:04:27,420 --> 00:04:27,880
Come on.

84
00:04:28,300 --> 00:04:30,220
Xiuxiu, I don't wanna go...

85
00:04:30,240 --> 00:04:32,300
Alright then... we're heading back.

86
00:04:33,570 --> 00:04:34,420
Take it.

87
00:04:35,260 --> 00:04:37,240
Wind's fierce out there—
no need to see us off.

88
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:38,130
We're leaving.

89
00:04:38,530 --> 00:04:39,460
Put your coat on.

90
00:04:42,280 --> 00:04:43,300
Take care on your way.

91
00:04:43,300 --> 00:04:44,100
We're off now!

92
00:04:53,700 --> 00:04:55,300
Can't bear to part with Susu?

93
00:04:55,540 --> 00:04:57,470
I'll fetch her back tomorrow then.

94
00:04:57,560 --> 00:04:58,880
This Mrs. Fei

95
00:04:59,100 --> 00:05:01,090
is the sturdiest lock in the Fei family.

96
00:05:01,090 --> 00:05:02,600
Everything—needing locking or not—

97
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:04,060
gets bolted shut under her watch.

98
00:05:04,060 --> 00:05:05,410
Now I can't even tell...

99
00:05:05,860 --> 00:05:08,190
Was letting Susu back to the Fei Residence

100
00:05:08,530 --> 00:05:10,130
really the right thing to do.

101
00:05:16,460 --> 00:05:17,720
Here, Sister-in-law.

102
00:05:18,850 --> 00:05:21,150
What's with suddenly wanting
to drink with me?

103
00:05:21,150 --> 00:05:22,180
Nothing special.

104
00:05:22,200 --> 00:05:23,730
Just wanted to share a cup.

105
00:05:23,980 --> 00:05:25,710
Sister-in-law, a toast to you.

106
00:05:32,750 --> 00:05:34,460
If there's something,
just say it straight.

107
00:05:34,460 --> 00:05:36,060
No need for roundabout talk.

108
00:05:36,090 --> 00:05:38,890
If it's something I can help with,
of course I will.

109
00:05:39,360 --> 00:05:40,850
You saw right through me.

110
00:05:41,430 --> 00:05:42,830
Then I'll speak plainly—

111
00:05:44,700 --> 00:05:47,550
Feng Er wants to rent some good land
from you.

112
00:05:49,400 --> 00:05:51,400
Did Feng Er put you up to this,

113
00:05:51,420 --> 00:05:53,250
or was it your sister?

114
00:05:53,900 --> 00:05:55,530
Sister-in-law, you're so sharp!

115
00:05:55,530 --> 00:05:56,490
It was my sister.

116
00:05:58,240 --> 00:05:59,520
So your sister really plans

117
00:05:59,520 --> 00:06:01,380
to keep living with Feng Dajiao?

118
00:06:01,400 --> 00:06:02,160
Of course!

119
00:06:02,440 --> 00:06:04,530
My brother-in-law treats her so well now.

120
00:06:04,530 --> 00:06:05,650
And I can see

121
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:07,410
my sister genuinely loves him.

122
00:06:07,510 --> 00:06:09,440
They're truly happy together now!

123
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:12,120
That's good then.

124
00:06:12,920 --> 00:06:13,810
Sister-in-law,

125
00:06:13,810 --> 00:06:15,160
about the land...

126
00:06:18,900 --> 00:06:19,620
I agree.

127
00:06:19,700 --> 00:06:20,590
Really?

128
00:06:21,850 --> 00:06:23,380
When have I ever lied to you?

129
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:25,330
Besides, it's all family land.

130
00:06:25,340 --> 00:06:27,200
Just a matter of lifting a finger.

131
00:06:27,340 --> 00:06:28,460
You've already promised them.

132
00:06:28,460 --> 00:06:29,950
I won't make you lose face.

133
00:06:30,310 --> 00:06:31,680
Thank you, Sister-in-law!

134
00:06:31,680 --> 00:06:33,740
I'll toast you on my sister's behalf.

135
00:06:51,480 --> 00:06:52,880
What's the deal, Feng Si?

136
00:06:54,350 --> 00:06:56,480
I told Kuangzi to invite you for drinks

137
00:06:57,440 --> 00:06:58,970
right after New Year's Eve—

138
00:07:00,090 --> 00:07:02,290
but it took me two days to track you down!

139
00:07:03,330 --> 00:07:06,030
Big shot now, huh?
Our drinks ain't fancy enough?

140
00:07:06,030 --> 00:07:07,830
Oh, I—I wouldn't dare!

141
00:07:08,520 --> 00:07:11,520
If you wouldn't dare,
then why are you here in my place?

142
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:14,600
Come here.

143
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:15,190
Sit!

144
00:07:16,540 --> 00:07:17,200
Take a seat.

145
00:07:17,950 --> 00:07:18,470
Come on.

146
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:21,460
I'll just... sit here.

147
00:07:27,620 --> 00:07:28,890
Our fathers

148
00:07:30,120 --> 00:07:31,830
dealt with each other
for half their lives.

149
00:07:31,830 --> 00:07:33,120
I still remember—

150
00:07:34,390 --> 00:07:35,790
around the New Year time,

151
00:07:35,860 --> 00:07:38,330
the only one drinking
and talking with my father...

152
00:07:38,330 --> 00:07:39,300
was yours.

153
00:07:41,130 --> 00:07:41,770
What?

154
00:07:43,170 --> 00:07:45,340
You married off both daughters,

155
00:07:45,930 --> 00:07:47,409
and now at New Year's—

156
00:07:47,659 --> 00:07:51,100
not even your son is home
to drink and talk with you?

157
00:07:54,950 --> 00:07:57,750
Guess it's just us two now,

158
00:07:58,310 --> 00:07:59,370
eating, drinking, and
shooting the breeze—

159
00:07:59,370 --> 00:08:01,940
like my old man and yours back then.

160
00:08:02,340 --> 00:08:03,340
I remember...

161
00:08:04,510 --> 00:08:06,750
when your dad drank at our place,

162
00:08:08,530 --> 00:08:11,060
we'd always pack him
some peanuts when he left

163
00:08:11,520 --> 00:08:12,650
for his youngest son

164
00:08:13,060 --> 00:08:15,540
at home.

165
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:18,290
Is that true?

166
00:08:20,630 --> 00:08:22,430
Did you eat them all?

167
00:08:23,550 --> 00:08:24,070
Did you?

168
00:08:28,060 --> 00:08:29,790
With mother and father gone...

169
00:08:30,400 --> 00:08:33,000
no one left in this world
who truly cares for me.

170
00:08:35,120 --> 00:08:38,030
Your father—now there was a real farmer.

171
00:08:39,390 --> 00:08:41,250
Everyone for miles knew his name.

172
00:08:42,520 --> 00:08:43,679
Feng the Iron Pole—

173
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,830
strong as an ox, that man.

174
00:08:46,810 --> 00:08:48,130
I remember when my father

175
00:08:48,130 --> 00:08:49,840
young and hot-headed,

176
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:53,480
challenged yours
to a wheat-cutting contest.

177
00:08:53,480 --> 00:08:54,270
That sun...

178
00:08:54,870 --> 00:08:55,530
merciless.

179
00:08:55,610 --> 00:08:58,400
But your father just stripped his shirt,
soaked it in water,

180
00:08:58,400 --> 00:09:00,310
tied it around his head,

181
00:09:00,330 --> 00:09:01,180
bent his back—

182
00:09:07,790 --> 00:09:09,720
and cleared 3 mu
without a break.

183
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:12,290
Your father

184
00:09:12,640 --> 00:09:14,160
was truly admirable.

185
00:09:14,530 --> 00:09:16,890
He left you a great inheritance too.

186
00:09:17,630 --> 00:09:18,240
Come on,

187
00:09:18,260 --> 00:09:18,930
Feng Si.

188
00:09:22,310 --> 00:09:24,910
Let's drink to our fathers—yours and mine.

189
00:09:31,080 --> 00:09:33,220
Our families, generation after generation,

190
00:09:33,220 --> 00:09:34,430
rooted in this same village...

191
00:09:34,430 --> 00:09:37,400
That's the kind of bond
that weathers all storms.

192
00:09:37,980 --> 00:09:38,640
Here you go.

193
00:09:38,660 --> 00:09:39,540
You like this.

194
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:41,410
Have more!

195
00:09:52,930 --> 00:09:54,660
All this talk of 'old bonds'...

196
00:09:55,320 --> 00:09:56,250
yet you're still

197
00:09:56,450 --> 00:09:57,780
hounding me over debts?

198
00:09:59,030 --> 00:10:01,080
Eyeing my last few mus too?

199
00:10:01,390 --> 00:10:02,720
You fool.

200
00:10:03,450 --> 00:10:04,980
You think I covet your land?

201
00:10:05,810 --> 00:10:07,650
A sharp mind like yours—

202
00:10:07,870 --> 00:10:09,790
can't you see what's really happening?

203
00:10:09,790 --> 00:10:11,960
I'm doing this
for your father's sake!

204
00:10:12,760 --> 00:10:13,900
He gave you all the good fields,

205
00:10:13,900 --> 00:10:16,500
but tell me—can you even
farm or maintain them?

206
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:24,530
You mentioned that
when Dajiao was just born,

207
00:10:25,190 --> 00:10:27,470
his feet were big as a four-year-old's?

208
00:10:29,250 --> 00:10:31,030
He had one foot come out first at birth—

209
00:10:31,030 --> 00:10:33,230
scared the midwife half to death!

210
00:10:33,530 --> 00:10:35,050
But the real wonder?

211
00:10:35,550 --> 00:10:37,000
This child could sprint

212
00:10:37,210 --> 00:10:39,730
around the yard at eight months old.

213
00:10:40,040 --> 00:10:41,790
Those feet grew wild—

214
00:10:41,820 --> 00:10:44,100
I couldn't sew shoes fast enough.

215
00:10:45,010 --> 00:10:48,090
By nine, he wore his father's size!

216
00:10:48,120 --> 00:10:49,580
With those giant paddles,

217
00:10:50,320 --> 00:10:52,200
no village kid

218
00:10:52,230 --> 00:10:54,220
at his age could

219
00:10:54,240 --> 00:10:56,120
outrun him.

220
00:10:56,960 --> 00:10:59,820
Mountain climbs,
tree scaling, and river fishing.

221
00:11:00,170 --> 00:11:01,410
he's always number 1.

222
00:11:02,390 --> 00:11:04,790
Folks said those big feet
kept him rooted.

223
00:11:05,290 --> 00:11:06,170
I remember—

224
00:11:07,100 --> 00:11:08,270
back when we were kids,

225
00:11:08,270 --> 00:11:10,820
he once raced my brother's horse!

226
00:11:10,820 --> 00:11:12,350
I was the one who stopped it.

227
00:11:12,460 --> 00:11:13,620
I said it was unfair.

228
00:11:15,070 --> 00:11:16,180
So what happened next?

229
00:11:16,180 --> 00:11:17,860
Did his feet just stop growing?

230
00:11:17,860 --> 00:11:20,070
Stopped at 18...

231
00:11:20,350 --> 00:11:23,230
though I swear lately
they've shrunk a tad.

232
00:11:25,390 --> 00:11:27,550
Then tell me more about

233
00:11:27,910 --> 00:11:29,220
those immortals.

234
00:11:30,700 --> 00:11:31,910
Why the rush?

235
00:11:33,310 --> 00:11:35,970
Are you so eager to learn
about Dajiao's legend?

236
00:11:36,340 --> 00:11:38,340
If you're tired, we can stop for now.

237
00:11:38,430 --> 00:11:39,150
Not at all.

238
00:11:39,390 --> 00:11:41,340
Talking about my boy? Never tired!

239
00:11:42,220 --> 00:11:44,270
Back when Dajiao was five,

240
00:11:44,550 --> 00:11:45,740
it was also a winter.

241
00:11:46,460 --> 00:11:49,030
Under Grandpa Ox, west of the village,

242
00:11:49,030 --> 00:11:51,630
he saved a starving beggar, passed out,

243
00:11:51,860 --> 00:11:53,430
days without food or water,

244
00:11:54,740 --> 00:11:57,030
rags barely hanging off him,

245
00:11:57,030 --> 00:11:58,390
face gaunt,

246
00:11:58,670 --> 00:12:00,500
barely breathing,

247
00:12:00,860 --> 00:12:02,270
almost a goner.

248
00:12:02,950 --> 00:12:04,620
Kind-hearted Dajiao

249
00:12:05,270 --> 00:12:06,800
kept running back and forth

250
00:12:07,030 --> 00:12:08,270
from the house

251
00:12:08,270 --> 00:12:10,070
with steamed buns and hot water,

252
00:12:10,100 --> 00:12:12,740
eventually dragging that man back
from death's door.

253
00:12:12,740 --> 00:12:15,070
When the man woke, he didn't thank Dajiao.

254
00:12:15,340 --> 00:12:18,070
Just made him kneel, kowtow,
and call him master.

255
00:12:18,150 --> 00:12:21,070
And Dajiao? He did it.

256
00:12:21,070 --> 00:12:22,910
That man slept 7 days

257
00:12:22,910 --> 00:12:23,860
in our woodshed,

258
00:12:24,430 --> 00:12:25,620
in the hay pile.

259
00:12:26,550 --> 00:12:29,430
By day, he'd take Dajiao
around everywhere.

260
00:12:30,340 --> 00:12:31,550
Then, on the 7th day,

261
00:12:31,820 --> 00:12:34,270
that man vanished without a word.

262
00:12:34,670 --> 00:12:36,190
No idea where he went.

263
00:12:37,270 --> 00:12:38,310
After that,

264
00:12:38,720 --> 00:12:40,620
your father-in-law and I started noticing—

265
00:12:40,620 --> 00:12:43,310
our boy had new skills.

266
00:12:43,480 --> 00:12:44,910
He could cure a sick ox,

267
00:12:45,620 --> 00:12:46,860
spot-on.

268
00:12:47,270 --> 00:12:49,860
He could read the clouds
to predict weather.

269
00:12:50,650 --> 00:12:52,610
But he picked up a strange habit too.

270
00:12:52,610 --> 00:12:53,990
Every few days, he'd go sweep

271
00:12:53,990 --> 00:12:57,060
around the Grandpa Ox statue,
clean it up real nice.

272
00:12:58,100 --> 00:13:00,300
Even made offerings during festivals.

273
00:13:00,460 --> 00:13:01,960
Folks laughed, called him crazy.

274
00:13:01,960 --> 00:13:03,390
He didn't care.

275
00:13:04,150 --> 00:13:05,880
When he was little, I asked him,

276
00:13:06,270 --> 00:13:07,910
"Why do you do this?"

277
00:13:08,220 --> 00:13:10,620
He told me, "My master's still here.

278
00:13:11,100 --> 00:13:12,860
The Grandpa Ox is my master."

279
00:13:13,500 --> 00:13:16,100
When he got older,
he stopped talking about it.

280
00:13:16,460 --> 00:13:17,920
But I've always wondered—

281
00:13:19,620 --> 00:13:21,880
was that an immortal showing him the way?

282
00:13:24,620 --> 00:13:25,220
Good girl.

283
00:13:25,790 --> 00:13:27,790
You're such a smart girl!

284
00:13:28,030 --> 00:13:30,740
You spun it even better than I did—see?

285
00:13:32,380 --> 00:13:33,950
I learned it all from you.

286
00:13:34,460 --> 00:13:35,220
Not at all.

287
00:13:36,790 --> 00:13:37,910
That's really nice.

288
00:13:37,910 --> 00:13:40,270
Back when Dajiao was little,
he was such a good boy—

289
00:13:40,270 --> 00:13:41,390
so dutiful, so filial,

290
00:13:41,390 --> 00:13:43,340
and a real talent in the fields.

291
00:13:43,700 --> 00:13:46,220
And now he married you.

292
00:13:46,340 --> 00:13:47,940
Although you're a fine lady—

293
00:13:47,960 --> 00:13:49,790
you take to everything just right.

294
00:13:49,790 --> 00:13:52,740
your future's brighter than sunshine.

295
00:13:56,790 --> 00:13:59,430
You both are really calm.

296
00:14:00,390 --> 00:14:01,390
What's going on?

297
00:14:01,910 --> 00:14:03,390
I want Xiuxiu

298
00:14:03,740 --> 00:14:05,340
to visit her younger sister.

299
00:14:05,670 --> 00:14:07,030
-For what?
-For what?

300
00:14:07,980 --> 00:14:09,310
For the land obviously!

301
00:14:10,220 --> 00:14:12,150
Otherwise—you think it's for you?

302
00:14:12,670 --> 00:14:14,000
Have you heard about it?

303
00:14:14,390 --> 00:14:17,670
The Cao family
started surveying land for deeds.

304
00:14:17,930 --> 00:14:19,410
I suppose, next step,

305
00:14:19,430 --> 00:14:21,640
the big landlords will follow soon.

306
00:14:22,340 --> 00:14:25,030
If the Fei family does the same…

307
00:14:25,340 --> 00:14:28,130
We're done! The good lands will vanish!

308
00:14:28,270 --> 00:14:30,070
That's why we must send Xiuxiu.

309
00:14:30,070 --> 00:14:32,130
We've got connections—let's use it.

310
00:14:33,670 --> 00:14:34,270
Father.

311
00:14:35,150 --> 00:14:37,210
Didn't Susu agree just the other day?

312
00:14:37,350 --> 00:14:40,280
Let's give her time
to discuss it with Mrs. Fei first.

313
00:14:40,700 --> 00:14:43,910
What's the point of going now
if they haven't sorted things out yet?

314
00:14:43,910 --> 00:14:45,390
We'll just end up a laughingstock!

315
00:14:45,390 --> 00:14:45,860
True.

316
00:14:45,860 --> 00:14:46,620
Be patient.

317
00:14:47,310 --> 00:14:49,100
Look at you—eyes popping so wide!

318
00:14:49,100 --> 00:14:50,620
Quit scaring us like that.

319
00:14:51,220 --> 00:14:53,220
Xiuxiu already said

320
00:14:53,220 --> 00:14:54,340
she'll wait for the right time.

321
00:14:54,340 --> 00:14:56,090
It's only Day 3 of New Year—

322
00:14:56,120 --> 00:14:58,260
let people at least
finish their celebration!

323
00:14:58,260 --> 00:14:59,460
Your father-in-law,

324
00:14:59,740 --> 00:15:01,290
the moment land is mentioned,

325
00:15:01,290 --> 00:15:03,570
he goes off like a monkey's ass on fire!

326
00:15:04,510 --> 00:15:05,710
Stop that ass saying!

327
00:15:08,340 --> 00:15:09,100
Okay.

328
00:15:09,270 --> 00:15:10,150
Alright.

329
00:15:10,150 --> 00:15:11,270
My bad. It's my bad.

330
00:15:11,270 --> 00:15:13,130
I shouldn't have undermined you—

331
00:15:13,150 --> 00:15:14,030
this… this head of the family dignity—

332
00:15:14,030 --> 00:15:15,620
especially in front of the youngsters.

333
00:15:15,620 --> 00:15:17,080
Enough with the nonsense.

334
00:15:17,740 --> 00:15:18,220
Anyway—

335
00:15:19,310 --> 00:15:20,150
where's Dajiao?

336
00:15:20,150 --> 00:15:21,480
Tietou called him over,

337
00:15:21,620 --> 00:15:23,620
saying they needed to check
his 13 mu of land—

338
00:15:23,620 --> 00:15:25,820
to decide what to plant for quick cash.

339
00:15:27,220 --> 00:15:28,480
I‘ve seen it for years—

340
00:15:28,950 --> 00:15:29,700
Feng Si

341
00:15:30,550 --> 00:15:32,910
out there working odd jobs:

342
00:15:33,670 --> 00:15:36,740
hosting weddings,
funerals, running errands...

343
00:15:37,310 --> 00:15:38,310
No doubt,

344
00:15:38,920 --> 00:15:40,850
you're a true man of the world,

345
00:15:40,910 --> 00:15:42,550
all about pomp and circumstance.

346
00:15:42,550 --> 00:15:45,550
Honestly, sticking you in a field
is a waste of talent.

347
00:15:49,460 --> 00:15:51,190
When the family split the land,

348
00:15:52,550 --> 00:15:53,930
you got the best plots—

349
00:15:54,790 --> 00:15:56,220
so you'd thrive

350
00:15:56,220 --> 00:15:58,100
with a better life.

351
00:15:58,740 --> 00:15:59,620
But now look!

352
00:15:59,860 --> 00:16:00,820
That worthless land

353
00:16:00,820 --> 00:16:02,070
feels like it's…

354
00:16:02,070 --> 00:16:03,860
like it's got you leashed, huh?

355
00:16:04,460 --> 00:16:05,310
What a shame.

356
00:16:06,620 --> 00:16:08,310
I used to have over 20 mu—

357
00:16:08,610 --> 00:16:10,970
all handed to you.

358
00:16:11,030 --> 00:16:12,670
Now I'm left with just 4 mu.

359
00:16:13,730 --> 00:16:15,250
I've failed my father…

360
00:16:16,180 --> 00:16:16,910
Feng Si,

361
00:16:17,740 --> 00:16:18,980
do you still remember

362
00:16:20,270 --> 00:16:22,670
what your father said on his deathbed?

363
00:16:23,070 --> 00:16:24,820
Sell 5 mu to me.

364
00:16:25,390 --> 00:16:26,700
Your father knew—

365
00:16:27,500 --> 00:16:28,740
I honor old ties.

366
00:16:28,740 --> 00:16:31,740
I'd nurture your land right:

367
00:16:32,460 --> 00:16:35,550
rest it three years, ease it two…

368
00:16:35,550 --> 00:16:37,390
But that's not something you could do.

369
00:16:37,390 --> 00:16:38,700
First, you have no idea about it.

370
00:16:38,700 --> 00:16:39,340
Second,

371
00:16:40,030 --> 00:16:41,690
it's indeed a waste of talent.

372
00:16:42,010 --> 00:16:43,490
You belong out there,

373
00:16:44,170 --> 00:16:45,300
chasing quick cash—

374
00:16:46,030 --> 00:16:48,490
the faster you earn,
the sharper you'll get.

375
00:16:49,500 --> 00:16:50,430
Enough talk.

376
00:16:51,040 --> 00:16:52,550
Do whatever you want—

377
00:16:52,740 --> 00:16:53,910
not my problem.

378
00:16:54,650 --> 00:16:55,450
Here. Drink.

379
00:17:07,530 --> 00:17:08,089
Feng Si,

380
00:17:08,430 --> 00:17:10,589
here's a thought—

381
00:17:11,020 --> 00:17:13,060
why not hand that land to me?

382
00:17:13,829 --> 00:17:14,960
I'll tend it proper.

383
00:17:15,450 --> 00:17:16,560
Come harvest,

384
00:17:17,060 --> 00:17:17,980
send your wife and kids

385
00:17:17,980 --> 00:17:19,500
to collect their share.

386
00:17:19,500 --> 00:17:21,430
You keep hustling out there,
making fast cash.

387
00:17:21,430 --> 00:17:22,430
Everybody wins.

388
00:17:31,060 --> 00:17:32,260
Are we done drinking?

389
00:17:40,390 --> 00:17:40,980
Feng Si,

390
00:17:41,470 --> 00:17:42,320
look here—

391
00:17:43,220 --> 00:17:44,540
this is your land deed.

392
00:17:45,300 --> 00:17:46,760
Once the land's restored,

393
00:17:47,130 --> 00:17:48,330
I'll return it to you.

394
00:17:48,590 --> 00:17:49,850
You'll return it to me?

395
00:17:50,240 --> 00:17:52,770
Not now—I can't give it yet.

396
00:17:55,630 --> 00:17:56,630
Here's the thing:

397
00:17:57,780 --> 00:17:59,870
when you're tired of hustling out there,

398
00:17:59,870 --> 00:18:01,330
ready to retire back home,

399
00:18:01,780 --> 00:18:03,310
that's when I'll return it.

400
00:18:03,640 --> 00:18:04,710
If I handed it over now,

401
00:18:04,710 --> 00:18:06,170
you'd just gamble it away—

402
00:18:06,350 --> 00:18:08,210
and all my effort would be wasted!

403
00:18:13,110 --> 00:18:15,150
But give me your current plot,

404
00:18:15,540 --> 00:18:16,830
and I've done the math—

405
00:18:17,260 --> 00:18:19,390
with what you've already signed over,

406
00:18:19,780 --> 00:18:22,540
I can throw in extra bushels yearly.

407
00:18:22,540 --> 00:18:23,780
That's not an issue here.

408
00:18:23,780 --> 00:18:27,040
From then on, your family wouldn't even
need to touch a hoe.

409
00:18:36,430 --> 00:18:37,430
I've always said—

410
00:18:37,630 --> 00:18:39,300
I won't end up like Feng Er,

411
00:18:39,300 --> 00:18:41,630
face buried in dirt,
obsessed with planting crops.

412
00:18:41,630 --> 00:18:43,490
He's got a lump of soil for brains.

413
00:18:43,740 --> 00:18:44,400
My brother,

414
00:18:45,350 --> 00:18:46,390
you're right.

415
00:18:46,980 --> 00:18:49,980
I've got to chase fast money.

416
00:18:53,630 --> 00:18:54,430
Feng Si,

417
00:18:54,890 --> 00:18:58,130
press your thumb here—
we'll each keep a copy.

418
00:18:58,590 --> 00:19:00,260
No take-backs.

419
00:19:00,540 --> 00:19:03,740
You'll be the first in this whole village
to live easy.

420
00:19:28,300 --> 00:19:29,460
No take-backs.

421
00:19:35,330 --> 00:19:36,200
No farming!

422
00:19:38,870 --> 00:19:40,190
Chase fast money!

423
00:19:45,590 --> 00:19:47,060
Are you giving me money right now?

424
00:19:47,060 --> 00:19:48,260
For these 4 mu of land,

425
00:19:49,700 --> 00:19:50,940
I'll pay top price—

426
00:19:51,980 --> 00:19:53,780
5 silver dollars per mu.

427
00:19:54,170 --> 00:19:56,010
Four times five makes twenty.

428
00:19:57,510 --> 00:19:59,980
You owe me 15 dollars.

429
00:20:01,590 --> 00:20:02,850
Press your thumb here,

430
00:20:03,140 --> 00:20:04,580
take 5 dollars now,

431
00:20:05,450 --> 00:20:06,490
and we're square.

432
00:20:19,260 --> 00:20:19,910
Kuangzi.

433
00:20:23,260 --> 00:20:24,060
It's settled.

434
00:20:24,540 --> 00:20:25,150
Master.

435
00:20:26,260 --> 00:20:26,990
Send him off—

436
00:20:27,830 --> 00:20:29,430
and pack him all the peanuts.

437
00:20:30,460 --> 00:20:32,650
Oh, and wrap up
that legless chicken too.

438
00:20:32,650 --> 00:20:33,110
Okay.

439
00:20:34,260 --> 00:20:35,260
Wait for me, then.

440
00:20:37,030 --> 00:20:37,750
My brother,

441
00:20:39,260 --> 00:20:41,460
we get to drink till the world goes soft.

442
00:20:46,140 --> 00:20:49,070
This is it—no more drinks
with the Feng family for me,

443
00:20:49,660 --> 00:20:51,630
not today, not ever.

444
00:20:59,380 --> 00:21:00,250
Have some now.

445
00:21:01,220 --> 00:21:02,430
Back so late—

446
00:21:04,190 --> 00:21:06,320
did you and Tietou settle on the crops?

447
00:21:08,110 --> 00:21:09,980
Tietou was stalling…

448
00:21:10,430 --> 00:21:11,830
I knew something was off!

449
00:21:12,460 --> 00:21:13,540
Turns out—he can't even afford

450
00:21:13,540 --> 00:21:14,700
this year's seeds.

451
00:21:15,060 --> 00:21:15,790
What's more,

452
00:21:16,170 --> 00:21:18,370
Tietou's mom owes money left and right—

453
00:21:18,500 --> 00:21:19,500
asked around for credit on seeds,

454
00:21:19,500 --> 00:21:21,830
but no one's willing to provide on credit.

455
00:21:22,350 --> 00:21:23,260
What to do then?

456
00:21:24,830 --> 00:21:26,890
I thought he would hit me up for money—

457
00:21:27,110 --> 00:21:29,370
but he didn't mention a word till the end.

458
00:21:29,870 --> 00:21:30,630
I guess

459
00:21:30,870 --> 00:21:33,390
Tietou values you as a brother
and cares about you—

460
00:21:33,390 --> 00:21:35,980
He's afraid borrowing money
would just make things awkward.

461
00:21:35,980 --> 00:21:37,780
Tietou isn't that complicated—

462
00:21:38,200 --> 00:21:40,330
he's just too proud to spit it out.

463
00:21:40,910 --> 00:21:42,740
If only he could get seed money
without having to beg…

464
00:21:42,740 --> 00:21:45,350
That would be really nice.

465
00:21:45,590 --> 00:21:46,260
True.

466
00:21:46,590 --> 00:21:47,780
Help a man work,

467
00:21:48,540 --> 00:21:50,000
not just feed his poverty.

468
00:21:50,830 --> 00:21:53,390
But where's this easy money
he's supposed to make?

469
00:21:53,390 --> 00:21:55,630
If it existed,
we'd have jumped on it already.

470
00:21:55,630 --> 00:21:56,790
Weaving reed rain cloaks?

471
00:21:56,790 --> 00:21:58,450
Not exactly the season for it.

472
00:21:58,640 --> 00:21:59,370
Besides,

473
00:22:00,260 --> 00:22:01,870
that Humpback Guo won't even take

474
00:22:01,870 --> 00:22:03,430
Tietou's mother's cloaks—

475
00:22:03,700 --> 00:22:05,350
says they're full of splinters,

476
00:22:05,350 --> 00:22:06,460
itch to wear.

477
00:22:11,060 --> 00:22:12,790
Here—take a look at my weaving.

478
00:22:17,540 --> 00:22:19,260
This rain reed rain cloak's woven tight!

479
00:22:19,260 --> 00:22:19,790
How is it?

480
00:22:20,210 --> 00:22:22,200
No wonder mother's been singing
your praises lately.

481
00:22:22,200 --> 00:22:23,330
She taught me well.

482
00:22:26,110 --> 00:22:27,350
Look at this!

483
00:22:27,980 --> 00:22:29,150
I told you to wrap it with cloth—

484
00:22:29,150 --> 00:22:30,260
why wouldn't you do that?

485
00:22:30,260 --> 00:22:32,590
Wrapping cloth messes up the weave—

486
00:22:34,500 --> 00:22:35,390
Mother says,

487
00:22:35,590 --> 00:22:36,670
winter reeds

488
00:22:36,780 --> 00:22:38,340
are not as pliant.

489
00:22:38,950 --> 00:22:40,350
All beginners struggle.

490
00:22:40,460 --> 00:22:42,390
I'll be fine with more experience.

491
00:22:42,590 --> 00:22:44,110
Let's just stop, alright?

492
00:22:44,740 --> 00:22:47,540
If you really must weave,
wait till after harvest.

493
00:22:48,210 --> 00:22:49,450
I won't let your hands

494
00:22:49,870 --> 00:22:51,270
turn into vulture claws!

495
00:22:52,740 --> 00:22:55,140
They'll end up like vulture claws someday.

496
00:22:55,460 --> 00:22:56,350
So be it.

497
00:22:58,910 --> 00:22:59,670
From now on,

498
00:23:00,140 --> 00:23:02,500
I'll handle the money hustle.

499
00:23:03,390 --> 00:23:04,110
Worst case—

500
00:23:04,540 --> 00:23:06,470
I'll haul goods with Humpback Guo.

501
00:23:06,870 --> 00:23:08,930
I don't want you to suffer this grind.

502
00:23:09,590 --> 00:23:11,060
Now you got me thinking—

503
00:23:12,180 --> 00:23:15,180
what if we send Tietou
to haul goods with Humpback Guo?

504
00:23:17,250 --> 00:23:18,140
That's an idea!

505
00:23:31,630 --> 00:23:32,100
Xiu—

506
00:23:33,980 --> 00:23:35,380
Today's Start of Spring.

507
00:23:36,020 --> 00:23:38,820
Mother asks you
to bite of the ritual radish first.

508
00:23:42,630 --> 00:23:44,870
Back home on the Start of Spring,

509
00:23:45,350 --> 00:23:47,300
Mother would make me chomp radishes, too—

510
00:23:47,300 --> 00:23:49,500
said it'd shake off spring drowsiness.

511
00:23:51,870 --> 00:23:52,800
What's so funny?

512
00:23:53,260 --> 00:23:54,110
Mother says

513
00:23:54,870 --> 00:23:57,670
this spring radish is also called
Descendant Radish.

514
00:23:57,670 --> 00:23:59,150
You eat it,

515
00:23:59,390 --> 00:24:00,260
so she can

516
00:24:00,670 --> 00:24:02,070
have a grandbaby sooner.

517
00:24:02,920 --> 00:24:04,720
Now chew the radish—no more lip!

518
00:24:07,830 --> 00:24:08,300
Oh—

519
00:24:08,700 --> 00:24:10,260
and Father's testing the spring's breath.

520
00:24:10,260 --> 00:24:10,700
What?

521
00:24:10,700 --> 00:24:11,150
Move it, move it!

522
00:24:11,150 --> 00:24:12,410
What spring's breath?

523
00:24:40,350 --> 00:24:44,720
♪ The moon leans gently over the valley, ♪

524
00:24:45,450 --> 00:24:49,350
♪ Showing me this weathered land. ♪

525
00:24:50,160 --> 00:24:53,600
♪ Years rise and fall like the tides ♪

526
00:24:53,620 --> 00:24:57,870
♪ Yet here, my heart finds home ♪

527
00:24:58,880 --> 00:25:03,190
♪ All things grow and fade in season, ♪

528
00:25:03,980 --> 00:25:08,030
♪ But life's dance never ends ♪

529
00:25:08,630 --> 00:25:11,280
♪ Such radiance ♪

530
00:25:11,440 --> 00:25:16,930
♪ Where I and all living things ♪

531
00:25:16,950 --> 00:25:21,330
♪ Race toward the vast unknown ♪

532
00:25:21,710 --> 00:25:25,800
♪ Our sweat soaking time's satchel ♪

533
00:25:26,740 --> 00:25:27,220
♪ How long a life must stretch ♪

534
00:25:27,220 --> 00:25:28,750
Spring's breath is moving!

535
00:25:29,970 --> 00:25:35,010
♪ I measure it in golden grain ♪

536
00:25:35,710 --> 00:25:40,010
♪ Light a lantern, look back ♪

537
00:25:40,290 --> 00:25:45,220
♪ The land's rings etch
the mountains' spine ♪

538
00:25:45,220 --> 00:25:45,630
Great!

539
00:25:45,630 --> 00:25:48,810
♪ Holding up the undying sun ♪

540
00:25:49,080 --> 00:25:53,540
♪ Gifting us spring light
and wheat waves ♪

541
00:25:54,090 --> 00:25:56,330
♪ Light a lantern, look back ♪

542
00:25:56,330 --> 00:25:58,090
Beat the spring ox!

543
00:25:58,670 --> 00:25:58,880
Beat the spring ox!

544
00:25:58,880 --> 00:26:00,700
♪ The land's rings etch
the mountains' spine ♪

545
00:26:00,700 --> 00:26:02,430
Laziness flees!

546
00:26:02,590 --> 00:26:04,200
Laziness flees!

547
00:26:04,200 --> 00:26:04,910
♪ Holding up the undying sun ♪

548
00:26:04,910 --> 00:26:06,260
Plow the fields hard!

549
00:26:06,260 --> 00:26:07,390
Plow the fields hard!

550
00:26:07,390 --> 00:26:07,550
Plow the fields hard!

551
00:26:07,550 --> 00:26:08,190
♪ Gifting us spring light
and wheat waves ♪

552
00:26:08,190 --> 00:26:09,950
Harvest comes rich!

553
00:26:10,150 --> 00:26:12,500
Harvest comes rich!

554
00:26:12,870 --> 00:26:17,430
One strike—rains and winds obey!

555
