556
00:26:20,430 --> 00:26:22,540
I remember that spring—

557
00:26:22,980 --> 00:26:24,780
the first time in my life

558
00:26:25,150 --> 00:26:26,780
I truly felt the testing
of spring's breath.

559
00:26:26,780 --> 00:26:29,830
♪ Race toward the vast unknown ♪

560
00:26:29,830 --> 00:26:31,230
The first time I sensed

561
00:26:31,230 --> 00:26:31,670
♪ Our sweat soaking time's satchel ♪

562
00:26:31,670 --> 00:26:33,910
the land's urgent thirst for sowing.

563
00:26:34,630 --> 00:26:35,630
And I saw—

564
00:26:35,630 --> 00:26:36,430
♪ How long a life must stretch ♪

565
00:26:36,430 --> 00:26:38,840
how the farmers,
reading the soil's shifts,

566
00:26:38,840 --> 00:26:40,110
♪ I measure it in golden grain ♪

567
00:26:40,110 --> 00:26:44,190
showed their fierce,
tender care for this earth.

568
00:26:44,990 --> 00:26:45,060
♪ Light a lantern, look back ♪

569
00:26:45,060 --> 00:26:46,740
They listened to

570
00:26:46,740 --> 00:26:48,780
every faint pulse of the ground,

571
00:26:49,110 --> 00:26:49,640
and labored to nourish

572
00:26:49,640 --> 00:26:50,830
♪ The land's rings etch
the mountains' spine ♪

573
00:26:50,830 --> 00:26:53,060
each flicker of life in it.

574
00:26:53,500 --> 00:26:55,000
That's when I understood:

575
00:26:55,000 --> 00:26:57,590
♪ Holding up the undying sun ♪

576
00:26:57,590 --> 00:26:58,300
this land

577
00:26:58,300 --> 00:26:58,590
♪ Gifting us spring light
and wheat waves ♪

578
00:26:58,590 --> 00:26:59,980
isn't just

579
00:26:59,980 --> 00:27:02,190
the farmers' lifeline.

580
00:27:02,630 --> 00:27:04,110
It's the very place

581
00:27:04,390 --> 00:27:06,460
where they root their souls.

582
00:27:07,220 --> 00:27:09,190
Everyone's here,

583
00:27:10,020 --> 00:27:12,350
the New Year's celebration is done,
so let's settle rents.

584
00:27:12,350 --> 00:27:14,280
If you missed last year's payment,

585
00:27:14,740 --> 00:27:16,540
you lose 30% of your leased land.

586
00:27:17,260 --> 00:27:20,060
Missed two years for last year
and the year before?

587
00:27:20,220 --> 00:27:21,480
Half your plot's gone.

588
00:27:21,910 --> 00:27:22,670
But if

589
00:27:23,020 --> 00:27:24,590
you insist on keeping the land,

590
00:27:24,590 --> 00:27:25,870
this year's rent

591
00:27:26,260 --> 00:27:27,950
goes up by one extra bushel.

592
00:27:29,350 --> 00:27:31,910
As everyone knows,

593
00:27:32,160 --> 00:27:34,160
our Madam
is the fairest landlord

594
00:27:34,370 --> 00:27:35,920
among neighbor villages.

595
00:27:35,980 --> 00:27:36,720
Am I right about it?

596
00:27:36,720 --> 00:27:37,750
Yes, that's true.

597
00:27:38,590 --> 00:27:39,870
Now—if you understand,

598
00:27:39,870 --> 00:27:41,830
step up and sign
the new lease.

599
00:27:42,110 --> 00:27:43,110
Thumbprint here.

600
00:27:43,700 --> 00:27:44,430
Come up here.

601
00:27:44,680 --> 00:27:45,280
I'll do it.

602
00:27:52,040 --> 00:27:52,950
Madam is here!

603
00:27:54,780 --> 00:27:55,870
Mrs. Fei.

604
00:27:56,460 --> 00:27:57,460
Tietou's mother,

605
00:27:57,870 --> 00:27:59,200
here to talk to me again?

606
00:28:01,590 --> 00:28:02,590
Madam, please—

607
00:28:02,740 --> 00:28:04,740
have some mercy on us.

608
00:28:05,390 --> 00:28:07,390
We paid our rent last year,

609
00:28:07,390 --> 00:28:09,220
and this year too.

610
00:28:09,740 --> 00:28:12,150
It's just…
when that no-good Tietou's father

611
00:28:12,150 --> 00:28:13,110
got sick,

612
00:28:13,110 --> 00:28:14,980
we borrowed a bit extra from you.

613
00:28:15,300 --> 00:28:16,910
If not for those old debts—

614
00:28:16,910 --> 00:28:19,170
Old debts, new debts—
debts all the same.

615
00:28:20,010 --> 00:28:22,300
Your family's never paid rent in full,

616
00:28:22,540 --> 00:28:24,800
and every year
I've rounded down for you.

617
00:28:25,260 --> 00:28:27,460
But I can't keep swallowing losses.

618
00:28:28,180 --> 00:28:29,140
This year—

619
00:28:29,460 --> 00:28:31,450
you'll decide: plant or not,

620
00:28:31,670 --> 00:28:33,220
but under my terms.

621
00:28:33,220 --> 00:28:34,080
We surly plant.

622
00:28:34,500 --> 00:28:37,110
I'll go talk to Tietou—
we'll find a way.

623
00:28:37,350 --> 00:28:39,660
The land must be sown…
it must.

624
00:28:40,630 --> 00:28:41,430
Beard Liu,

625
00:28:41,900 --> 00:28:43,870
if Feng Er arrives, show him in.

626
00:28:43,930 --> 00:28:44,680
Roger that.

627
00:28:45,230 --> 00:28:46,080
Madam!

628
00:28:46,100 --> 00:28:47,330
Hold on there, Feng Er!

629
00:28:47,330 --> 00:28:47,740
Madam.

630
00:28:47,740 --> 00:28:49,700
Madam requests your presence inside
for a conversation.

631
00:28:49,700 --> 00:28:50,350
Sure.

632
00:28:50,520 --> 00:28:51,340
Hold on please.

633
00:28:51,340 --> 00:28:53,330
Since this is your first year
of leasing our land,

634
00:28:53,330 --> 00:28:53,630
Yes.

635
00:28:53,630 --> 00:28:54,700
Madam wishes

636
00:28:54,700 --> 00:28:56,740
to clarify certain expectations.

637
00:28:56,740 --> 00:28:57,350
By the way,

638
00:28:57,970 --> 00:29:01,410
she'll also discuss
autumn harvest procedures in detail.

639
00:29:01,590 --> 00:29:03,000
Thank you, Big Jowl.

640
00:29:03,020 --> 00:29:04,150
Thanks a lot.

641
00:29:04,150 --> 00:29:05,080
You're welcome.

642
00:29:06,370 --> 00:29:07,170
Watch the way.

643
00:29:12,440 --> 00:29:13,040
Come on in.

644
00:29:13,540 --> 00:29:14,400
Xiu, he's here.

645
00:29:15,490 --> 00:29:15,970
Come in.

646
00:29:17,730 --> 00:29:19,380
Xiuxiu, don't mess with me—

647
00:29:19,690 --> 00:29:21,090
that Humpback Guo
swears

648
00:29:21,500 --> 00:29:23,500
he'll only team up

649
00:29:23,500 --> 00:29:24,550
with his own blood.

650
00:29:24,550 --> 00:29:26,310
Humpback Guo was just joking—

651
00:29:26,340 --> 00:29:27,450
all talk, no bite.

652
00:29:28,730 --> 00:29:29,140
Look—

653
00:29:29,590 --> 00:29:31,220
I packed you a bundle.

654
00:29:32,640 --> 00:29:33,770
This padded jacket?

655
00:29:34,040 --> 00:29:35,610
your brother wore it last winter,

656
00:29:35,610 --> 00:29:37,000
but I've ripped out the old lining
and scrubbed it clean.

657
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:38,260
If you don't mind hand-me-downs,

658
00:29:38,260 --> 00:29:39,460
it'll do for the road.

659
00:29:42,630 --> 00:29:43,830
Did it actually work?

660
00:29:45,910 --> 00:29:47,120
Great, let me try.

661
00:29:48,070 --> 00:29:48,880
No rush.

662
00:29:49,170 --> 00:29:51,400
Now, there are rules on the road—

663
00:29:52,180 --> 00:29:54,330
you'll need to hear Dajiao's instructions.

664
00:29:54,330 --> 00:29:55,820
Once he's briefed you properly,

665
00:29:55,820 --> 00:29:58,550
go to Humpback Guo's place
and sign the contract.

666
00:29:58,590 --> 00:30:00,310
Long as it puts cash in my hand,

667
00:30:00,540 --> 00:30:02,000
I'll follow any damn rule.

668
00:30:03,980 --> 00:30:04,500
Xiuxiu,

669
00:30:05,060 --> 00:30:05,990
does it fit on me?

670
00:30:06,170 --> 00:30:06,900
Yes, it does.

671
00:30:07,990 --> 00:30:10,250
Looks better on you
than it ever did on me.

672
00:30:23,150 --> 00:30:23,700
Settled.

673
00:30:24,480 --> 00:30:25,280
It's settled.

674
00:30:25,540 --> 00:30:26,470
What's settled?

675
00:30:26,960 --> 00:30:28,310
Mrs. Fei agreed—

676
00:30:28,690 --> 00:30:30,740
they'll lease us the land!

677
00:30:31,540 --> 00:30:32,980
Did she mention which plot of land?

678
00:30:32,980 --> 00:30:35,350
She didn't specify. Just said
she'd think it over.

679
00:30:35,350 --> 00:30:36,260
Screw the details—

680
00:30:36,260 --> 00:30:37,740
long as we get the land!

681
00:30:37,740 --> 00:30:39,060
Over 10 mu of land!

682
00:30:39,060 --> 00:30:42,320
Deed will be signed in three days,
with land to be received.

683
00:30:43,460 --> 00:30:45,500
Our daughter-in-law's a gem—

684
00:30:46,540 --> 00:30:48,580
pretty face,

685
00:30:48,610 --> 00:30:50,430
sharper wits.

686
00:30:50,540 --> 00:30:52,540
Rarer than a firefly in winter!

687
00:30:52,540 --> 00:30:54,300
Whose kin is she?

688
00:30:54,300 --> 00:30:56,360
The Feng family's prize, that's who!

689
00:30:57,110 --> 00:30:57,950
Of course.

690
00:30:57,950 --> 00:31:00,110
We've got 18 mu now—

691
00:31:00,220 --> 00:31:03,220
add Mrs. Fei's dozen or so,

692
00:31:03,430 --> 00:31:05,830
we'll be sleeping right
in the fields soon.

693
00:31:06,110 --> 00:31:07,110
Dajiao's mother!

694
00:31:07,590 --> 00:31:08,670
Cook the meals

695
00:31:09,020 --> 00:31:10,680
and deliver them to the field!

696
00:31:16,210 --> 00:31:17,250
Still awake?

697
00:31:18,390 --> 00:31:20,260
I've already slept a full round!

698
00:31:22,630 --> 00:31:23,740
Can't sleep.

699
00:31:24,500 --> 00:31:25,500
Just thinking—

700
00:31:26,110 --> 00:31:28,460
all that new land…

701
00:31:29,150 --> 00:31:31,350
my heart's pounding like a drum!

702
00:31:32,380 --> 00:31:33,350
No rest tonight.

703
00:31:33,540 --> 00:31:34,950
It's a done deal—

704
00:31:36,350 --> 00:31:37,500
no need to panic.

705
00:31:40,390 --> 00:31:41,700
A woman's mind—

706
00:31:42,350 --> 00:31:44,060
so many things

707
00:31:44,500 --> 00:31:46,060
going on in my own.

708
00:31:50,060 --> 00:31:50,870
Dajiao,

709
00:31:50,980 --> 00:31:52,500
I've done the sums—

710
00:31:52,870 --> 00:31:56,700
with these extra 10 mu
from Mrs. Fei,

711
00:31:56,870 --> 00:31:58,700
if the harvest's decent,

712
00:31:58,700 --> 00:32:00,300
we'll cover the rent

713
00:32:00,740 --> 00:32:02,070
and have grain to spare.

714
00:32:02,190 --> 00:32:05,110
Spare grain means profit.

715
00:32:05,110 --> 00:32:06,220
Profit means

716
00:32:06,220 --> 00:32:07,700
I can buy a few more fields.

717
00:32:08,000 --> 00:32:10,550
Add those to our 18 mu now…

718
00:32:10,580 --> 00:32:11,820
we'll top 20 mus!

719
00:32:12,830 --> 00:32:14,500
Now, with more than 10 mu
of new land to work on,

720
00:32:14,500 --> 00:32:16,230
I can make the most of my energy.

721
00:32:17,260 --> 00:32:18,920
There's more land to farm now.

722
00:32:19,220 --> 00:32:21,750
I'm worried
that it might tire you and Father.

723
00:32:22,060 --> 00:32:23,300
Tiredness doesn't bother me.

724
00:32:23,300 --> 00:32:25,900
Not having enough workload
is my only concern.

725
00:32:26,190 --> 00:32:28,390
I have more than
10 mu of land in my house.

726
00:32:28,460 --> 00:32:29,660
What wonderful news!

727
00:32:29,670 --> 00:32:31,070
But I've thought it over.

728
00:32:31,350 --> 00:32:34,110
No matter how hard you two men sweat,
it won't be enough.

729
00:32:34,110 --> 00:32:35,590
We got to share a plow team,

730
00:32:35,700 --> 00:32:37,150
using their livestock.

731
00:32:37,670 --> 00:32:38,300
Dajiao,

732
00:32:38,700 --> 00:32:40,950
you might need to have a talk with Zhuzi.

733
00:32:41,150 --> 00:32:42,520
His house is close to ours,

734
00:32:42,520 --> 00:32:44,190
and our fields are not far apart.

735
00:32:44,190 --> 00:32:45,670
If we team up in using livestock,

736
00:32:45,670 --> 00:32:48,430
shall the payment in money
or grain?

737
00:32:48,430 --> 00:32:50,290
We need to agree on it beforehand.

738
00:32:50,500 --> 00:32:52,300
I've always dreamed

739
00:32:52,590 --> 00:32:54,540
of owning an ox.

740
00:32:54,740 --> 00:32:55,350
With one,

741
00:32:56,570 --> 00:32:59,330
we'd sow whenever we want to.

742
00:32:59,620 --> 00:33:01,020
Buying an ox? Brilliant!

743
00:33:01,110 --> 00:33:02,240
Nothing beats an ox—

744
00:33:02,670 --> 00:33:03,850
saves labor, saves sweat, hauls goods,

745
00:33:03,850 --> 00:33:05,510
and tills fields like a champ!

746
00:33:05,780 --> 00:33:07,150
I'm just saying—

747
00:33:07,350 --> 00:33:08,740
not like I've got the money.

748
00:33:08,740 --> 00:33:10,870
My money is earmarked
for land.

749
00:33:11,190 --> 00:33:12,020
I have no money.

750
00:33:12,020 --> 00:33:13,150
Then tell me—

751
00:33:13,460 --> 00:33:15,740
isn't buying land
meant for a better life?

752
00:33:15,740 --> 00:33:17,220
How's an ox different?

753
00:33:17,300 --> 00:33:18,380
What's the divide?

754
00:33:18,540 --> 00:33:19,700
Here's my thinking—

755
00:33:20,190 --> 00:33:22,110
sharing an ox with Zhuzi's family
works fine.

756
00:33:22,110 --> 00:33:24,150
Come harvest,
we'll settle accounts…

757
00:33:24,150 --> 00:33:25,740
That saves ourselves
the price of a whole damn ox!

758
00:33:25,740 --> 00:33:27,350
I've heard good brothers,
dear neighbors,

759
00:33:27,350 --> 00:33:29,260
turn to bitter enemies

760
00:33:29,470 --> 00:33:32,190
over shared plow teams.

761
00:33:32,380 --> 00:33:34,780
Overthink it,
and you'll drown in trouble.

762
00:33:34,780 --> 00:33:35,780
With these muscles of mine,

763
00:33:35,780 --> 00:33:37,380
would 10 mu extra be an issue?

764
00:33:37,700 --> 00:33:40,150
Come spring, I'll break that soil!

765
00:33:41,150 --> 00:33:42,110
With the ox,

766
00:33:42,350 --> 00:33:43,700
the strength of yours and father's

767
00:33:43,700 --> 00:33:45,430
can be saved for better things.

768
00:33:45,480 --> 00:33:47,190
Wouldn't a lighter load
be sweet?

769
00:33:47,190 --> 00:33:48,250
A lighter load? Ha!

770
00:33:48,460 --> 00:33:50,390
Idleness and me—we're strangers.

771
00:33:50,910 --> 00:33:51,870
Dajiao's right—

772
00:33:52,020 --> 00:33:53,910
a real farmer can't sit idle.

773
00:33:53,910 --> 00:33:55,440
The soil's where we belong.

774
00:33:55,830 --> 00:33:57,390
I just don't get it—

775
00:33:57,830 --> 00:33:59,560
what's wrong with buying an ox?

776
00:33:59,830 --> 00:34:01,220
It'll work for you!

777
00:34:01,830 --> 00:34:03,960
After all, men worth more than beasts.

778
00:34:04,040 --> 00:34:04,800
Well said!

779
00:34:05,150 --> 00:34:06,670
Men outweigh beasts!

780
00:34:07,190 --> 00:34:08,980
Xiuxiu cares for you both,

781
00:34:08,980 --> 00:34:10,230
and you're too deaf to hear it.

782
00:34:10,230 --> 00:34:11,620
I think Xiuxiu is right.

783
00:34:11,670 --> 00:34:12,940
With extra land, if not an ox,

784
00:34:12,940 --> 00:34:13,980
what should you buy?

785
00:34:13,980 --> 00:34:16,040
Want an ox? You buy it! I have no money.

786
00:34:16,830 --> 00:34:18,100
Oh, I heard it—

787
00:34:18,500 --> 00:34:20,580
your silver dollars in the cash box

788
00:34:20,710 --> 00:34:23,110
are screaming your name with every rattle!

789
00:34:24,790 --> 00:34:25,909
Is that so?

790
00:34:26,400 --> 00:34:27,800
I wanna buy an ox.

791
00:34:27,880 --> 00:34:30,070
I wanna buy an ox. Ox!

792
00:34:30,100 --> 00:34:31,630
Why didn't I hear anything?

793
00:34:32,270 --> 00:34:32,909
Enough!

794
00:34:33,139 --> 00:34:34,179
Buy or not, that's your call.

795
00:34:34,179 --> 00:34:36,350
I'm done— off to check the fields.

796
00:34:36,460 --> 00:34:38,460
Put on that hat—don't catch a chill.

797
00:34:41,139 --> 00:34:41,659
Xiu,

798
00:34:42,139 --> 00:34:43,460
I know you meant well

799
00:34:43,920 --> 00:34:45,400
by what you said today—

800
00:34:45,949 --> 00:34:47,980
you're striving for a better life.

801
00:34:48,310 --> 00:34:51,040
But buying livestock…
that‘s no small decision.

802
00:34:51,389 --> 00:34:52,949
Haven't you heard the saying?

803
00:34:52,949 --> 00:34:55,880
"A fortune counts for nothing
if it walks on hooves."

804
00:34:56,100 --> 00:34:57,960
One plague hits,

805
00:34:58,100 --> 00:35:00,100
and the mightiest beast
drops dead—

806
00:35:00,710 --> 00:35:02,840
there goes your silver
down the river.

807
00:35:07,870 --> 00:35:09,800
Xiuxiu…
you're upset, aren't you?

808
00:35:11,020 --> 00:35:11,910
No, I'm not.

809
00:35:12,430 --> 00:35:13,290
Get some sleep.

810
00:35:18,850 --> 00:35:20,410
Fine ox! Fine ox!

811
00:35:20,440 --> 00:35:22,030
Step right up and see!

812
00:35:22,500 --> 00:35:24,620
Prime four-year-old beast—

813
00:35:24,620 --> 00:35:26,350
though its horn-tip's chipped,

814
00:35:26,350 --> 00:35:28,430
it'll plow straight as an arrow!

815
00:35:29,460 --> 00:35:30,230
Come take a look!

816
00:35:30,230 --> 00:35:32,270
Zhang Hoof!
Stop your hollering—

817
00:35:32,500 --> 00:35:33,870
how many days
have you hawked this beast?

818
00:35:33,870 --> 00:35:34,270
Exactly!

819
00:35:34,270 --> 00:35:35,870
Who would buy a single-horned ox?

820
00:35:35,870 --> 00:35:36,580
True.

821
00:35:36,580 --> 00:35:37,270
So what?

822
00:35:37,540 --> 00:35:38,790
I'll sell my single-horned ox my way.

823
00:35:38,790 --> 00:35:40,140
Not your business.

824
00:35:40,830 --> 00:35:43,160
If it won't sell… I'll butcher it
for meat.

825
00:35:43,310 --> 00:35:44,110
Got a problem?

826
00:35:44,870 --> 00:35:46,580
Check out the single-horned ox!

827
00:35:46,580 --> 00:35:47,140
Have a look!

828
00:35:47,140 --> 00:35:48,800
I'll admit—it's a fine beast…

829
00:35:48,850 --> 00:35:51,170
pity about that missing horn.

830
00:35:51,580 --> 00:35:52,460
Exactly!

831
00:35:52,460 --> 00:35:53,540
Every day it's unsold,

832
00:35:53,540 --> 00:35:54,820
it guzzles good grain.

833
00:35:54,820 --> 00:35:56,100
Slaughtering it is just a problem of time.

834
00:35:56,100 --> 00:35:56,830
Exactly!

835
00:35:58,460 --> 00:35:59,830
How much is this ox?

836
00:36:00,230 --> 00:36:00,790
Ah, here!

837
00:36:02,540 --> 00:36:04,200
Miss Xiuxiu. What sharp eyes!

838
00:36:04,390 --> 00:36:05,650
A true judge of cattle.

839
00:36:05,660 --> 00:36:07,500
This ox is thick fat,

840
00:36:07,620 --> 00:36:08,660
with solid muscle.

841
00:36:08,660 --> 00:36:10,920
There's absolutely no issue
for it to plow.

842
00:36:10,920 --> 00:36:12,760
Seeing you're serious…

843
00:36:12,790 --> 00:36:13,830
six silver dollars. Deal?

844
00:36:13,830 --> 00:36:14,960
Six silver dollars?

845
00:36:16,270 --> 00:36:18,100
Well, the difference is way too big.

846
00:36:18,100 --> 00:36:19,870
I have only 1 silver dollar on me.

847
00:36:19,870 --> 00:36:21,100
Only 1 silver dollar?

848
00:36:21,100 --> 00:36:22,540
Are you kidding me...

849
00:36:22,870 --> 00:36:25,310
But my father might
scrape together a bit more…

850
00:36:25,310 --> 00:36:26,910
This is a great ox!

851
00:36:27,180 --> 00:36:27,910
Miss Xiuxiu.

852
00:36:28,430 --> 00:36:30,060
What do you think about
that single-horned ox?

853
00:36:30,060 --> 00:36:31,520
We may go with a fair price.

854
00:36:32,460 --> 00:36:33,500
Single-horned…

855
00:36:34,500 --> 00:36:36,100
Doubt my father will accept.

856
00:36:36,310 --> 00:36:38,570
Unless the price makes him swallow hard.

857
00:36:38,660 --> 00:36:39,720
The price is right.

858
00:36:40,620 --> 00:36:41,660
Four silver dollars!

859
00:36:41,660 --> 00:36:42,860
Four silver dollars?

860
00:36:43,150 --> 00:36:45,810
Four silver dollars
for this single-horned ox?

861
00:36:46,630 --> 00:36:48,810
Face it—this ox will never sell.

862
00:36:49,390 --> 00:36:51,850
Every day it lingers,
it devours good grain.

863
00:36:51,950 --> 00:36:52,580
Better butcher it.

864
00:36:52,580 --> 00:36:53,270
Do you find it expensive
at 4 silver dollars?

865
00:36:53,270 --> 00:36:53,910
Hold on.

866
00:36:57,540 --> 00:36:58,500
We may go with 3 silver dollars.

867
00:36:58,500 --> 00:36:59,620
That's the lowest I can offer.

868
00:36:59,620 --> 00:37:00,480
How about that?

869
00:37:01,900 --> 00:37:03,960
It's a good ox. It works with no issue.

870
00:37:05,180 --> 00:37:06,460
Alright. Let me have a look.

871
00:37:06,460 --> 00:37:07,120
Take a look.

872
00:37:11,350 --> 00:37:12,310
What do you think about it?

873
00:37:12,310 --> 00:37:15,240
Although single-horned,
it shows strength at work.

874
00:37:22,020 --> 00:37:24,280
This ox seems to have taken
a liking to me.

875
00:37:25,710 --> 00:37:26,710
I'll take it then.

876
00:37:27,310 --> 00:37:29,110
But you—you need to do me a favor.

877
00:37:29,310 --> 00:37:30,140
This ox...

878
00:37:30,310 --> 00:37:32,100
You take it to my father yourself.

879
00:37:32,100 --> 00:37:33,540
He'll pay you the rest.

880
00:37:36,830 --> 00:37:38,870
But what if your father refuses it?

881
00:37:41,350 --> 00:37:42,980
Here's one silver dollar—

882
00:37:43,550 --> 00:37:44,550
call it a deposit.

883
00:37:44,930 --> 00:37:46,390
If my father really won't take it,

884
00:37:46,390 --> 00:37:47,590
you keep this dollar.

885
00:37:49,060 --> 00:37:49,660
Deal.

886
00:37:50,100 --> 00:37:51,500
Then we call it a deal.

887
00:37:51,620 --> 00:37:52,350
Yes, deal.

888
00:37:56,540 --> 00:37:57,600
Single-horned ox.

889
00:38:08,430 --> 00:38:09,430
Is anyone home?

890
00:38:11,620 --> 00:38:12,660
Anyone there?

891
00:38:14,500 --> 00:38:16,020
The ox is here.

892
00:38:16,210 --> 00:38:17,380
Whose ox is this?

893
00:38:17,830 --> 00:38:19,560
This household just bought it.

894
00:38:19,960 --> 00:38:20,930
How great.

895
00:38:20,950 --> 00:38:22,140
What ox is here?

896
00:38:24,430 --> 00:38:25,230
Hello?

897
00:38:31,500 --> 00:38:32,700
What ox is this?

898
00:38:33,390 --> 00:38:34,790
It's the ox of your household.

899
00:38:34,790 --> 00:38:35,710
Feng Er

900
00:38:36,060 --> 00:38:37,980
rented land and even bought an ox!

901
00:38:37,980 --> 00:38:38,830
That's great!

902
00:38:39,300 --> 00:38:40,200
Wait, Feng Er.

903
00:38:40,500 --> 00:38:42,100
Why is this ox missing a horn?

904
00:38:43,960 --> 00:38:46,220
Missing a horn, but it's strong for work!

905
00:38:46,460 --> 00:38:47,430
Exactly!

906
00:38:47,430 --> 00:38:48,910
Why is it single-horned?

907
00:38:49,130 --> 00:38:49,930
Hold on there.

908
00:38:50,580 --> 00:38:53,500
Why do you bring this ox to my house?

909
00:38:54,270 --> 00:38:56,540
Your daughter-in-law
bought this ox for your family.

910
00:38:56,540 --> 00:38:57,790
She asked me to deliver it.

911
00:38:57,790 --> 00:38:59,720
Said you'd inspect it and pay cash.

912
00:39:00,350 --> 00:39:02,080
My daughter-in-law bought it?

913
00:39:03,020 --> 00:39:04,430
And she wanted me to inspect it?

914
00:39:04,430 --> 00:39:04,980
That's right.

915
00:39:04,980 --> 00:39:06,510
And she wanted me to pay you?

916
00:39:08,500 --> 00:39:09,560
No, I don't want it.

917
00:39:09,580 --> 00:39:10,540
You may take it back.

918
00:39:10,540 --> 00:39:12,180
I never said I would buy it. Take it away.

919
00:39:12,180 --> 00:39:12,980
That won't do!

920
00:39:13,230 --> 00:39:14,790
I walked over 6 to 7 li

921
00:39:14,790 --> 00:39:15,580
just to get here!

922
00:39:15,580 --> 00:39:16,500
Your daughter-in-law promised—

923
00:39:16,500 --> 00:39:18,310
cash payment and a free dinner!

924
00:39:18,310 --> 00:39:19,970
That's the only reason I came!

925
00:39:20,270 --> 00:39:22,400
What else did my daughter-in-law say?

926
00:39:22,830 --> 00:39:23,390
My dau—

927
00:39:24,280 --> 00:39:25,060
where is she?

928
00:39:26,050 --> 00:39:28,180
How could she make the decision alone?

929
00:39:29,140 --> 00:39:30,600
Acting like the boss, huh?

930
00:39:30,710 --> 00:39:32,040
If it's about the money,

931
00:39:32,050 --> 00:39:33,740
go ask her for it!

932
00:39:34,020 --> 00:39:36,100
I don't want this ox—take it back!

933
00:39:37,390 --> 00:39:38,180
Such a great ox!

934
00:39:38,180 --> 00:39:39,230
No, I don't want it.

935
00:39:39,230 --> 00:39:41,460
Then that silver dollar stays with me.

936
00:39:41,460 --> 00:39:42,320
I'm outta here.

937
00:39:42,730 --> 00:39:43,920
Wait a minute!

938
00:39:44,950 --> 00:39:46,710
Did she give you a silver dollar?

939
00:39:46,710 --> 00:39:47,100
Yes.

940
00:39:47,100 --> 00:39:49,140
Who will deliver it without a deposit?

941
00:39:49,140 --> 00:39:50,710
You think hay and water grow on trees?

942
00:39:50,710 --> 00:39:52,310
Wait a minute. Here's the thing.

943
00:39:52,310 --> 00:39:53,620
I don't want this ox.

944
00:39:53,830 --> 00:39:55,950
Give us back that silver dollar.

945
00:39:56,310 --> 00:39:57,040
Give it back!

946
00:39:57,300 --> 00:39:59,190
No ox? No refund. I'm out.

947
00:39:59,210 --> 00:39:59,780
Father.

948
00:40:00,430 --> 00:40:01,290
It's a great ox.

949
00:40:02,270 --> 00:40:03,180
Great ox!

950
00:40:03,430 --> 00:40:04,230
Wait a second!

951
00:40:04,380 --> 00:40:04,970
Hold on!

952
00:40:09,600 --> 00:40:10,500
This is a great ox.

953
00:40:10,500 --> 00:40:11,020
That's true.

954
00:40:11,020 --> 00:40:13,140
This ox is missing a horn!

955
00:40:13,140 --> 00:40:15,310
You really think it's worth full price?

956
00:40:15,310 --> 00:40:16,390
Are you trying to scam me?

957
00:40:16,390 --> 00:40:19,310
Hey now, I don't like that tone.

958
00:40:19,310 --> 00:40:21,270
If it weren't
for your daughter-in-law's kindness,

959
00:40:21,270 --> 00:40:23,020
I wouldn't even sell this low.

960
00:40:23,230 --> 00:40:24,610
Take it or leave it – I'm walking.

961
00:40:24,610 --> 00:40:25,410
Hold on there.

962
00:40:26,300 --> 00:40:27,760
Let's have a private talk.

963
00:40:30,540 --> 00:40:31,340
How much is it?

964
00:40:38,100 --> 00:40:38,950
I'll take it.

965
00:40:40,170 --> 00:40:41,370
I'll take it.

966
00:40:47,790 --> 00:40:49,450
This ox is really a great deal.

967
00:40:51,390 --> 00:40:53,250
Do you really think it's a good ox?

968
00:40:55,870 --> 00:40:57,270
Missing a horn, sure,

969
00:40:57,660 --> 00:40:59,270
but this is one fine ox!

970
00:40:59,830 --> 00:41:02,710
It's also a great deal
at 3 silver dollars.

971
00:41:04,310 --> 00:41:05,620
I've been thinking...

972
00:41:06,670 --> 00:41:09,370
I still want that silver dollar back.

973
00:41:10,600 --> 00:41:11,860
How's that gonna work?

974
00:41:11,980 --> 00:41:14,180
Father kept the ox only due to the pain

975
00:41:14,580 --> 00:41:17,280
that dollar deposit caused his soul.

976
00:41:18,270 --> 00:41:19,950
Probably still fuming now.

977
00:41:21,870 --> 00:41:23,870
Or, shall I give you a silver dollar?

978
00:41:27,460 --> 00:41:29,500
Why didn't I feel Father is mad?

979
00:41:30,350 --> 00:41:32,230
This is her acting on her own!

980
00:41:32,230 --> 00:41:34,710
We're talking 3 silver dollars here!

981
00:41:35,140 --> 00:41:37,620
Nobody held a knife to your throat.

982
00:41:37,830 --> 00:41:40,360
You opened the cash box yourself,
didn't you?

983
00:41:40,950 --> 00:41:42,230
If I don't pay up now,

984
00:41:42,230 --> 00:41:43,910
that silver dollar deposit

985
00:41:44,140 --> 00:41:45,460
goes straight to their pocket!

986
00:41:45,460 --> 00:41:46,860
Furthermore! Just look—

987
00:41:47,140 --> 00:41:49,910
Feasting and drinking guests,
all that good food and liquor...

988
00:41:49,910 --> 00:41:51,310
You know what that costs?

989
00:41:51,620 --> 00:41:53,020
That's real money!

990
00:41:53,390 --> 00:41:55,590
And she didn't even count the expenses!

991
00:41:57,580 --> 00:41:59,870
You—quit grinning! What's so funny?

992
00:42:01,750 --> 00:42:04,390
Seems Xiuxiu knows you best—

993
00:42:04,620 --> 00:42:06,830
she's got you wrapped around her finger.

994
00:42:06,830 --> 00:42:10,180
After decades
of your penny-pinching with me,

995
00:42:10,340 --> 00:42:12,120
finally, someone's putting you
in your place!

996
00:42:12,120 --> 00:42:13,950
What's wrong with being thrifty?

997
00:42:13,950 --> 00:42:15,660
What's wrong with it?

998
00:42:15,870 --> 00:42:16,730
Isn't it right?

999
00:42:16,980 --> 00:42:18,620
As the old saying goes:

1000
00:42:19,140 --> 00:42:20,950
"You won't be poor
from eating or drinking,

1001
00:42:20,950 --> 00:42:22,430
but poor planning will sink you."

1002
00:42:22,430 --> 00:42:23,910
Poor! Poor! Poor!

1003
00:42:24,140 --> 00:42:26,200
This girl... She's getting too wild.

1004
00:42:27,310 --> 00:42:28,540
I'll have Dajiao

1005
00:42:28,910 --> 00:42:30,370
knock some sense into her.

1006
00:42:33,390 --> 00:42:34,580
Where are you heading?

1007
00:42:34,580 --> 00:42:35,310
I need to pee.

1008
00:42:37,310 --> 00:42:39,540
I knew you couldn't hold out.

1009
00:42:56,320 --> 00:42:57,800
A hornless ox,

1010
00:42:58,750 --> 00:43:00,230
a squint-eyed man—

1011
00:43:01,620 --> 00:43:03,480
these are creatures with temper!

1012
00:43:04,140 --> 00:43:05,500
And temper?

1013
00:43:06,140 --> 00:43:08,100
That's just personality in disguise.
